---
title: Corn & Refried Bean Quesadillas with Creamy Guac & Smoky Crema
description: Quick and easy meals are fine for sustenance but they’re not always exciting, you know? Not these quesadillas, though! These gooey, griddled beauts feel luxurious and nourishing, yet take only 15 minutes to make, thanks to smart techniques like charring corn for smoky-sweet depth and smart shortcuts like ready-made refried beans, guac, and red pepper crema. Of course, all the cheese melding the filling together doesn’t hurt!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/corn-refried-bean-quesadillas-0baa0f0e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/corn-refried-bean-quesadillas-625ed3d315f6f31a6c446581-cf968530.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/corn-and-refried-bean-quesadillas-625ed3d315f6f31a6c446581
author: HelloFresh
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: Mexican
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 840 kcal
  fat: 50 g
  saturated fat: 22 g
  carbohydrates: 71 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 27 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 1900 mg
servings: 2
---

Drain @corn kernels{13.4%ounce}, then pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over high heat. Add corn and season with
@Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon} and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until charred, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Cover pan if corn begins to pop!

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a medium #bowl{} and set aside. Wipe out pan.

While corn chars, place @refried beans{16%ounce} in a second medium #microwave-safe bowl{}. Stir in
@Mexican Spice Blend{1%tablespoon} and @water{1%TBSP}. Microwave for
~{2%minutes}; stir to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface; evenly spread half the
refried bean mixture (all for 4 servings) over each tortilla. Evenly top one half of
each tortilla with half the @Mexican cheese blend{1%cup}. Top with half the corn
(all for 4), then sprinkle with remaining cheese. Fold each tortilla in half to
create quesadillas.

> You may have some extra beans and corn—serve on the side!

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for corn over
medium-high heat. Add quesadillas; cook until tortillas are golden brown and
cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

While quesadillas cook, in a small bowl, combine @guacamole{4%tablespoon} and
@sour cream{2%tablespoon}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Cut quesadillas into wedges and divide between plates. Serve with creamy guac and
@smoky red pepper crema{4%tablespoon} on the side for dipping.